    "back": "Where a wife (or cohabitant) charges her interest in the family home to secure her partner's business debts, the lender is put on inquiry that the surety's consent may have been procured by undue influence. To avoid being affected by the undue influence, the lender must ensure the surety received independent legal advice. If the lender fails to take these steps, the mortgage/charge is voidable at the surety's instance.",
