    "back": "The House of Lords confirmed the long-standing rule that the burden of a positive covenant does not run with freehold land — neither at common law nor in equity. A covenant to keep a roof in repair, made between the original parties, could not be enforced against a successor in title to the covenantor's land. Only the benefit (not the burden) of positive covenants runs.",
